  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 435 mg
---

Preheat oven to 400 degrees (200c). Core, seed, and remove the white ribs from the
@red bell pepper{1}(cored, seeded, and white ribs removed), then thinly slice.
Halve, peel, and thinly slice the @yellow onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).
Cut the @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%oz} into ½-inch cubes. Finely chop the @cilantro{8%g}(finely chopped).
Cut the @lemon{1} into wedges.

Toss the potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with @olive oil{1%tbsp} and season with
@salt{} and @black pepper{}. Place in the oven and roast for ~{15-20%minutes},
tossing halfway through, until golden brown.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add the
@green beans{4%oz}, onion, and bell pepper and cook, tossing, ~{7-8%minutes},
until softened and slightly blistered. Stir in half the chopped cilantro, season
with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, and set aside.

In the same pan, heat another @olive oil{1%tbsp} over medium-high heat. Season
the @catfish{12%oz} on all sides with the @blackening spice{1%tsp}, @salt{},
and @black pepper{}. Add the catfish to the pan and cook ~{3-4%minutes} per
side, until cooked through and slightly blackened.

Plate the potatoes and blistered vegetables, then top with the blackened
catfish. Serve with lemon wedges, a sprinkle of the remaining cilantro, and
enjoy!